Installation instructions for macOS Logo
macOS
LibreWolf macOS RepositorySystem Requirements
HomeBrew
LibreWolf is available via HomeBrew by entering:

brew install --cask librewolf
It is possible that Apple Silicon users see their recently installed LibreWolf flagged as broken. More details are available in our FAQ.

Disk Image
You can also install LibreWolf via a .dmg, but please note that this method requires to apply updates manually.

Download librewolf-106.0.2-1.en-US.mac.x86_64.dmgView all versions and release notes

Compiling from source
Instructions for building LibreWolf from source on macOS can be found in the build guide. This method is strongly suggested, especially on M1 powered machines, where the compile time is rather short.
